8. quid, si ferant: 86. dicas. The subj. preS. cloes not 11616 suggest that the hypothesis is merely imaginary, butferaut is attracted into the mood of dicas: ‘if you were to learn this, you would say ' etc. Several good MSS. omit si and have et in line 9, and some have quodsi here, which facts seem to point to some corruption.
